JavaScript doesn't have `abstract` classes, but you can simulate them by throwing in the base class method:

```js
speak() {
  throw new Error('speak() must be implemented by subclass');
}
```

Forget to implement it in a subclass and you'll get a clear error — not a silent undefined.

